*[[1691]] &amp;ndash; [[George Fox]], English founder of Quakerism (b. 1624)
*[[1717]] &amp;ndash; [[Maria Sibylla Merian]], naturalist and scientific illustrator (b. 1647)
*[[1766]] &amp;ndash; [[Frederick V of Denmark|King Frederick V of Denmark]] (b. 1723)
*[[1775]] &amp;ndash; [[Johann Georg Walch]], German theologian (b. 1693)
*[[1790]] &amp;ndash; [[Luc Urbain de Bouexic, comte de Guichen]], French admiral (b. 1712)
*[[1796]] &amp;ndash; [[John H. D. Anderson]], Scottish scientist and inventor (b. 1726)
*[[1797]] &amp;ndash; [[Elisabeth Christine von Braunschweig-Bevern]], wife of [[Frederick II of Prussia]] (b. 1715)
*[[1832]] &amp;ndash; [[Thomas Lord]], English cricketer, founder of [[Lord's cricket ground]] (b. 1755)
*[[1838]] &amp;ndash; [[Ferdinand Ries]], German composer (b. 1784)
*[[1852]] &amp;ndash; [[Fabian Gottlieb von Bellingshausen]], Russian explorer (b. 1778)
*[[1853]] &amp;ndash; [[Theophilos Kairis]], Greek priest, humanist and revolutionary (b. 1783)
*[[1860]] &amp;ndash; [[William Mason (US politician)|William Mason]], American politician (b. 1786)
*[[1864]] &amp;ndash; [[Stephen Foster]], American composer (b. 1826)
*[[1882]] &amp;ndash; [[Wilhelm Mauser]], German weapon designer and manufacturer (b. 1834)
*[[1885]] &amp;ndash; [[Schuyler Colfax]], American politician (b. 1823)
*[[1889]] &amp;ndash; [[Solomon Bundy]], American politician (b. 1823)
*[[1894]] &amp;ndash; [[Nadezhda von Meck]], Russian patroness of [[Pyotr Tchaikovsky]] (b. 1831)
*[[1905]] &amp;ndash; [[George Thorn]], [[Premier of Queensland]] (b. 1838)
*[[1906]] &amp;ndash; [[Alexander Stepanovich Popov]], Russian physicist (b. 1859)
*[[1915]] &amp;ndash; [[Mary Slessor]], Scottish missionary (b. 1848)
*[[1923]] &amp;ndash; [[Alexandre Ribot]], French statesman (b. 1842)
*[[1924]] &amp;ndash; [[Georg Hermann Quincke]], German physicist (b. 1834)
*[[1928]] &amp;ndash; [[Mara Buneva]],  Bulgarian revolutionary (b. 1902)
*[[1929]] &amp;ndash; [[Wyatt Earp]], American Western lawman (b. 1848)
*  1929   &amp;ndash; [[H. B. Higgins]], Australian politician and judge (b. 1851)
*[[1932]] &amp;ndash; [[Sophia of Prussia]], consort of [[Constantine I of Greece]] (b. 1870)
*[[1934]] &amp;ndash; [[Paul Ulrich Villard]], French physicist (b. 1860)
*[[1937]] &amp;ndash; [[Antoine Védrenne]], French rower (b. 1878)
*[[1941]] &amp;ndash; [[James Joyce]], Irish writer (b. 1882)
*[[1943]] &amp;ndash; [[Sophie Taeuber-Arp]], Swiss artist (b. 1889)
*[[1956]] &amp;ndash; [[Lyonel Feininger]], German-American painter and caricaturist (b. 1871)
*[[1958]] &amp;ndash; [[Jesse L. Lasky]], American film producer (b. 1880)
*[[1961]] &amp;ndash; [[Herman Glass]], American gymnast (b. 1880)
*[[1962]] &amp;ndash; [[Ernie Kovacs]], American actor and comedian (b. 1919)
*[[1967]] &amp;ndash; [[Anatole de Grunwald]], British producer and screenwriter (b. 1910)
*[[1971]] &amp;ndash; [[Robert Still]], English composer (b. 1910)
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; [[Raoul Jobin]], Canadian tenor (b. 1906)
*  1974   &amp;ndash; [[Salvador Novo]], Mexican writer and poet (b. 1904)
*[[1976]] &amp;ndash; [[Margaret Leighton]], English actress (b. 1922)
*[[1977]] &amp;ndash; [[Henri Langlois]], French film archivist, and a co-founder of the Cinémathèque Française (b. 1914)
*[[1978]] &amp;ndash; [[Hubert H. Humphrey]], 38th Vice President of the United States (b. 1911)
*  1978   &amp;ndash; [[Joe McCarthy (manager)|Joe McCarthy]], American baseball manager (b. 1887)
*[[1979]] &amp;ndash; [[Donny Hathaway]], American musician (b. 1945)
*  1979   &amp;ndash; [[Marjorie Lawrence]], Australian soprano (b. 1907)
*[[1980]] &amp;ndash; [[Andre Kostelanetz|André Kostelanetz]], Russian-born music conductor and arranger (b. 1901)
*[[1982]] &amp;ndash; [[Marcel Camus]], French director (b. 1912)
*  1982   &amp;ndash; [[Arland D. Williams, Jr.]], hero of [[Air Florida Flight 90]] (b. 1935)
*[[1988]] &amp;ndash; [[Chiang Ching-kuo]], President of the Republic of China (b. 1910)
*[[1993]] &amp;ndash; [[Camargo Guarnieri]], Brazilian composer (b. 1907)
*[[1995]] &amp;ndash; [[Max Harris (poet)|Max Harris]], Australian poet, columnist and publisher (b. 1921)
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; [[Michael Cuccione]], Canadian actor and singer ([[2ge+her]]) (b. 1985)
*[[2002]] &amp;ndash; [[Ted Demme]], American film director (b. 1963)
*  2002   &amp;ndash; [[Gregorio Fuentes]], Cuban fisherman, [[Ernest Hemingway|Ernest Hemingway's]] first mate (b. 1897)
*  2002   &amp;ndash; [[Frank Shuster]], Canadian comedian (b. 1916)
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; [[Norman Panama]], American screenwriter and director (b. 1914)
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; [[Arne Næss Jr.]], Norwegian mountain climber (b. 1937)
*  2004   &amp;ndash; [[Harold Shipman]], British serial killer (b. 1946)
*  2004   &amp;ndash; [[Zeno Vendler]], American philosopher of language (b. 1921)
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Earl Cameron (Canadian broadcaster)|Earl Cameron]], Canadian broadcaster (b. 1915)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[Nell Rankin]], American mezzo-soprano (b. 1924)
*[[2006]] &amp;ndash; [[Frank Fixaris]], American sportscaster (b. 1934)
*  2006   &amp;ndash; [[Marc Potvin]], Canadian ice hockey player (b. 1967)
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; [[Michael Brecker]], American jazz saxophonist (b. 1949)
*  2007   &amp;ndash; [[Danny Oakes]], American racecar driver (b. 1911)
*[[2008]] &amp;ndash; [[Sergejus Larinas|Sergei Larin]], Lithuanian tenor (b. 1956)
*  2008   &amp;ndash; [[Johnny Podres]], American baseball player (b. 1932)
*[[2009]] &amp;ndash; [[Doña Mary Ejercito]], Filipino supercentarian, mother of [[Joseph Ejercito Estrada]] (b. 1905)
*  2009   &amp;ndash; [[Dai Llewellyn]] Welsh socialite
*  2009   &amp;ndash; [[Patrick McGoohan]], American actor (b. 1928)
*  2009   &amp;ndash; [[Mansour Rahbani]], Lebanese composer and lyricist (b. 1925)
*  2009   &amp;ndash; [[Nancy Bird Walton]], Australian aviator (b. 1915)
*  2009   &amp;ndash; [[William De Witt Snodgrass]], American poet under the pseudonym S. S. Gardons (b. 1926)
*[[2010]] &amp;ndash; [[Teddy Pendergrass]], American R&amp;B singer ([[Harold Melvin &amp; The Blue Notes]]) (b. 1950)
*  2010   &amp;ndash; [[Jay Reatard]], American garage punk musician ([[The Reatards]] and [[Lost Sounds]]) (b. 1980)
*  2010   &amp;ndash; [[Kalifa Tillisi]], Libyan writer and linguist (b. 1930)
*[[2011]] &amp;ndash; [[Albert Heijn]], a Dutch entrepreneur, major stock holder and founder and chairman of the board of Ahold (b. 1927)
*[[2012]] &amp;ndash; [[Rauf Denktaş]], Turkish Cypriot politician, founder and first president of [[Northern Cyprus]] (b. 1924)

